## Coding Style

- All errors returned from `RunE` are printed to stderr; do not use `fmt.Println` for errors
- Primary data to stdout; diagnostics, progress, and errors to stderr
- `SilenceUsage: true` on every `cobra.Command` with a `RunE` ‚Äî never dump usage on runtime errors
- Flag names are lowercase hyphenated (never camelCase)
- Define output structs early; human-readable tables are a rendering layer on top of them
- Respect `NO_COLOR` env and `--no-color` flag everywhere color is used
- Prompts only when `os.Stdin` is a TTY; `--no-input` disables all prompts
- Use `--dry-run` / `-n` before any state-changing operation

## Testing Guidelines

- Table-driven tests in `_test.go` files adjacent to the code under test
- Integration tests in `internal/‚Ä¶_test.go` tagged with `//go:build integration`
- Run unit tests only: `go test ./... -short`
- Run integration tests: `go test ./... -tags integration`
- Aim for ‚â• 70% coverage on `internal/`

## Commit & PR Guidelines

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):
`feat | fix | docs | refactor | test | chore | ci | build | style | perf`

PR description must include:
- What changed and why
- How it was tested
- Any new flags or breaking changes
